From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 19:46:51 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add runs prune subcommand for safe run cleanup
 (FR-E83)

Delete the oldest run directories under <workflow>/runs/ keeping the N
newest deletable runs, ordered by start time replayed from journal.jsonl.
Hard safety rules: non-terminal runs, the run referenced by runs/.lock,
and runs with missing/unreplayable journals are never deleted (reported
skipped with reason). --dry-run reports without deleting; --keep must be
a non-negative integer. Selection logic lives in src/state/prune.ts and
reuses getRunDir, replayRunJournal, and the lock helpers.

Docs: FR-E83 registered in the SRS (06-distribution-and-housekeeping);
plugin-distribution FRs E70-E72 split out to 06b-plugin-distribution.md
to stay within the per-file docs token budget; SDS module notes added.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
